Early forms , with complex vertebrae consisting of a number of separate elements , were placed in the suborder Rachitomi , and large Triassic aquatic forms with simpler vertebrae were placed in the suborder Stereospondyli . The basic rhachitomous condition is found in many primitive tetrapods , and is not unique to one group of temnospondyls . Moreover, the vertebrae of temnospondyls are often simpler than those of modern tetrapods , and some temnospondyls have a reduced number of vertebrae , as well as a reduced number of ribs . Therefore, the original suborder of temnospondyls was not strictly based on the number of vertebrae, but rather on the shape and complexity of the vertebrae.
